{"builtWith":"0.15.15","comments":[{"LineComment":" ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━"},{"LineComment":"                             // hydrogen // optimize // submodular // rounding"},{"LineComment":" ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━"},{"LineComment":" | Pipage Rounding for Submodular Maximization."},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | ## Theoretical Foundation"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | Pipage rounding converts fractional solutions to integral solutions while:"},{"LineComment":" | 1. Maintaining feasibility (output is always matroid-independent)"},{"LineComment":" | 2. Preserving marginals: E[1_e ∈ S] = x_e for all elements e"},{"LineComment":" | 3. Never decreasing expected value: E[f(S)] ≥ F(x)"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | The key insight: for submodular functions, the multilinear extension F"},{"LineComment":" | is concave along \"pipage\" directions (transfer probability between elements)."},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | ## Pipage Direction"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | A pipage step between elements i and j with transfer ε:"},{"LineComment":" |   x'_i = x_i + ε"},{"LineComment":" |   x'_j = x_j - ε"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | The multilinear extension F is piecewise linear along this direction."},{"LineComment":" | We move to a \"breakpoint\" where either x'_i ∈ {0,1} or x'_j ∈ {0,1}."},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | ## Swap Rounding"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | Randomized variant: at each step, randomly choose direction."},{"LineComment":" | Preserves marginals in expectation and produces independent set."},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | ## Contention Resolution"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | For online/parallel settings: resolve conflicting element selections"},{"LineComment":" | probabilistically while maintaining approximation guarantees."},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | ## References"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | - Ageev, Sviridenko. \"Pipage Rounding: A New Method of Constructing"},{"LineComment":" |   Algorithms with Proven Performance Guarantee\" J. Comb. Opt. 2004"},{"LineComment":" | - Chekuri, Vondrák, Zenklusen. \"Dependent Randomized Rounding via"},{"LineComment":" |   Exchange Properties of Matroids\" FOCS 2010"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | ## Module Structure"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | This is a leader module that re-exports from submodules:"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | - Hydrogen.Optimize.Submodular.Rounding.Util (utilities)"},{"LineComment":" | - Hydrogen.Optimize.Submodular.Rounding.Pairing (element pairing)"},{"LineComment":" | - Hydrogen.Optimize.Submodular.Rounding.Metrics (quality metrics)"},{"LineComment":" | - Hydrogen.Optimize.Submodular.Rounding.Pipage (pipage algorithm)"},{"LineComment":" | - Hydrogen.Optimize.Submodular.Rounding.Swap (swap algorithm)"},{"LineComment":" | - Hydrogen.Optimize.Submodular.Rounding.Contention (contention resolution)"},{"LineComment":" | - Hydrogen.Optimize.Submodular.Rounding.MinEnergy (FAA P3 min-energy)"}],"decls":[],"exports":[],"foreign":[],"imports":[{"annotation":{"meta":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[132,4],"start":[127,1]}},"moduleName":["Hydrogen","Optimize","Submodular","Rounding","Contention"]},{"annotation":{"meta":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[108,4],"start":[103,1]}},"moduleName":["Hydrogen","Optimize","Submodular","Rounding","Metrics"]},{"annotation":{"meta":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[141,4],"start":[134,1]}},"moduleName":["Hydrogen","Optimize","Submodular","Rounding","MinEnergy"]},{"annotation":{"meta":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[101,4],"start":[95,1]}},"moduleName":["Hydrogen","Optimize","Submodular","Rounding","Pairing"]},{"annotation":{"meta":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[117,4],"start":[110,1]}},"moduleName":["Hydrogen","Optimize","Submodular","Rounding","Pipage"]},{"annotation":{"meta":null,"sourceSpan":